{"doc":{"isMarkdown":false,"isTranslated":true,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"max","mdn_url":"/es/docs/Web/EXSLT/math/max","locale":"es","native":"Español","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p></p><div style=\"background:#f5f5f5; margin: 5px 0;\" id=\"sect1\">\n    <b><a href=\"/es/docs/Web/XSLT/Transforming_XML_with_XSLT#referencia_de_xslt.2fxpath\">Referencia de XSLT y XPath</a></b>: <a href=\"/es/docs/Web/XSLT/Element\">Elementos XSLT</a>, <a href=\"/es/docs/Web/EXSLT\">Funciones EXSLT</a>, <ahref=\" es=\"\" docs=\"\" web=\"\" xpath=\"\" funciones\"=\"\">XPath:Funciones, <a href=\"/es/docs/Web/XPath/Axes\">XPath:Ejes</a>\n</ahref=\"></div><br>\n <code>math:max()</code> devuelve el valor máximo de un conjunto de nodos (node-set).<p></p>\n\n<p>To compute the maximum value of the node-set, the node set is sorted into descending order as it would be using <code><a href=\"es/XSLT/sort\">xsl:sort()</a></code> with a data type of <code>number</code>. The maximum value is then the first node in the sorted list, converted into a number.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"sintaxis","title":"Sintaxis","isH3":false,"content":"<pre class=\"eval notranslate\">math:max(<em>conjuntoNodos</em>)\n</pre>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"argumentos","title":"Argumentos","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n <dt id=\"conjuntonodos\"><code><em>conjuntoNodos</em></code></dt>\n <dd>El conjunto de nodos cuyo valor más alto va a ser devuelto.</dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"devuelve","title":"Devuelve","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Un fragmento de árbol resultante que representa como una cadena el valor numérico del nodo valorado como más alto.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"definido_en","title":"Definido en","isH3":false,"content":"<p><a class=\"external\" href=\"http://www.exslt.org/math/functions/max/index.html\" rel=\" noopener\">EXSLT - MATH:MAX</a></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"implementaci.c3.b3n_en_gecko","title":"Implementación en Gecko","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Implementado en Gecko 1.9 y posteriores.</p>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Sintaxis","id":"sintaxis"},{"text":"Definido en","id":"definido_en"},{"text":"Implementación en Gecko","id":"implementaci.c3.b3n_en_gecko"}],"summary":"To compute the maximum value of the node-set, the node set is sorted into descending order as it would be using xsl:sort() with a data type of number. The maximum value is then the first node in the sorted list, converted into a number.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"math:max()","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"}],"source":{"folder":"es/web/exslt/math/max","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/es/web/exslt/math/max/index.html","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/commit/5fe4ab11259b37914fab41914e84897fea47d143","filename":"index.html"},"parents":[{"uri":"/es/docs/Web","title":"Tecnología para desarrolladores web"},{"uri":"/es/docs/Web/EXSLT","title":"EXSLT"},{"uri":"/es/docs/Web/EXSLT/math","title":"Math (math)"},{"uri":"/es/docs/Web/EXSLT/math/max","title":"max"}],"pageTitle":"max - EXSLT | MDN","noIndexing":false}}